```regex
\.usfm$([\w]{3})$
``` 

**Explanation:**


* `\`.usfm$`: This part matches the literal string ".usfm" at the end of the filename, ensuring it has the correct extension. The `$` anchor ensures it's at the very end.

* `(\[[\w]{3}\])`:  This captures the three-character code.
    * `[\w]{3}`: This matches any 3 alphanumeric characters (letters and digits), allowing for uppercase or lowercase.
    * The parentheses around `[\w]{3}` create a capturing group, allowing us to extract just that portion of the match.
